      "body": "This would be a great time to talk to some of the Alumni from the program.&nbsp; I have worked with several graduates of that program.<br /><br /><div class=\"quoteheader\"><div class=\"topslice_quote\">Quote</div></div><blockquote class=\"bbc_standard_quote\">In other words, what advice do you have for me/us at this point in our radiation protection career?</blockquote><div class=\"quotefooter\"><div class=\"botslice_quote\"></div></div><br />That's a really broad question.&nbsp; Spend a few hours reading some posts on this site. Questions along those lines have been answered several times.&nbsp; In order to get a better answer, you will need to give us a more specific question.<br /><br />Here it goes again:&nbsp; The largest employer of Jr RP Technicians is... drum roll please..... Bartlett. 800-225-0385<br />You can try Atlantic group as well.<br />Post your resume on NukeWorker.<br />Check the company sites for the Utilities you are looking to work for.<br />Send your resume to any company that posts an RP job opening.<br /><br />When at TVA, Volunteer for everything.&nbsp; Tell Bartlett you will take any job any where, that you just want to stay employed.<br />",
